Hi, 
I think there is a bug in method GetChildKeys of https://github.com/aspnet/Configuration/blob/dev/src/Config/ConfigurationProvider.cs.

According to the documentation, it supposes to return the list of keys for this provider.

Let's imagine that I have a provider that contains keys with names which contain semicolon in their name, e.g. part1:part2:part3
then if I do something like  

```
var result = new List<string>();
foreach (var provider in Configuration.Providers)
{
	foreach (var key in provider.GetChildKeys(Enumerable.Empty<string>(), null))
	{                        
		result.Add(key);
	}
}
return result;
```

It will return me just part1, cutting of the rest of the key name because of the delimiter.
So it doesn't return a full list of keys for this provider, but just names of parent "nodes" of the data used to populate a provider.

If this is expected, how do I iterate through a full key names then?

